<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 27 日星期六 15:18:00 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Turkiye Presidential Election Runoff: Who, When, Where, What to Expect]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110637609" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110639396_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_46b000f050ab43daf3b2c25e4a002e71.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110639378" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/turkiye-presidential-election-runoff-who-when-where-what-to-expect-1110637609.html?share-img=1110639378"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Vitaliy Belousov</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">在土耳其驻俄罗斯莫斯科大使馆的投票站，第二轮总统选举的提前投票期间可以看到选票。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Ballots are seen during the early voting at the second round of presidential elections at the polling station in the Turkish embassy in Moscow, Russia.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="在土耳其驻俄罗斯莫斯科大使馆的投票站，第二轮总统选举的提前投票期间可以看到选票。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110639396_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_5881bf10a9a61221a5ff2861b4f58b61.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110639396_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_3917c3ee4cb7d04097c3d8bc2f6df90b.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110639396_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_35b1dc64bc10dd9f22c94a8ccb0fa35c.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110639396_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_5881bf10a9a61221a5ff2861b4f58b61.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Vitaliy Belousov</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Oleg Burunov - Sputnik International" title="奥列格布鲁诺夫" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/09/0b/1080424846_0:0:2048:2048_100x100_80_0_0_3d7b461f8a98586fa3fe739930816aea.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">奥列格布鲁诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_burunov_oleg/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:o.burunov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">星期天，土耳其人在他们国家的第一次总统选举决选中投票，这将决定谁将在未来五年内掌舵该国。谁是候选人，他们应该如何表现才能确保获胜？ Sputnik 对这些问题和其他问题都有答案。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">超过 6400 万土耳其人将有资格在 5 月 28 日的决选中在近 192,000 个投票站投票，其中包括超过 600 万在 5 月 14 日第一轮投票时首次投票的选民。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> Turkiye 各地的投票将于当地时间上午 8 点（格林威治标准时间 0500）开始，并于当地时间下午 5 点（格林威治标准时间 1400）关闭。鉴于第一轮有 87.04% 的合格选民投票，预计投票率会很高。未来的获胜者必须获得简单多数票才能确保获胜。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">选举规则规定，关于投票的预测和评论在下午 6 点（格林威治标准时间 1300 点）之前被禁止，媒体只能在晚上 9 点（格林威治标准时间 1800 点）之前自由报道选举结果。然而，高级选举委员会可能允许媒体比预定时间更早地报道结果。<strong>周日投票</strong>的最终结果预计将于周一下午 3 点（格林威治标准时间 1200）公布。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><em>与此同时，上周六至少有 340 万居住在国外的土耳其人开始了总统决选投票。</em></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2"> Turkiye 为何面临第二轮？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">土耳其最高选举委员会于 5 月 15 日正式宣布，由于没有任何竞争者能够获得 50% 的选票，5 月 14 日在土耳其举行的总统选举进入了<strong>决选阶段</strong>。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “我们的组织根据目前的情况决定，在没有候选人获得 50% 选票的情况下，于 5 月 28 日星期日举行第二轮总统选举。这将是土耳其历史上的第一次”选举委员会主席 Ahmet Yener 告诉记者。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110637609" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/turkiye-presidential-election-runoff-who-when-where-what-to-expect-1110637609.html?share-block=1110637616" data-title="&amp;quot;Our organization decided on the basis of the current situation, when no candidate is gaining 50% of the votes, to hold the second round of the presidential election on Sunday, May 28. This will be for the first time in the history of Turkiye,&amp;quot; Ahmet Yener, the head of the election commission, told reporters."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在第一轮投票中，执政的正义与发展党（AKP）总统<em><strong>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</strong></em>获得了<strong>49.52%</strong>的选票，而他的主要挑战者、来自反对党共和人民党（CHP）<em><strong>的凯末尔·基利奇达罗格鲁</strong></em>获得了<strong>44.88% 的选票</strong>。落后的是 ATA Alliance 候选人<em>Sinan Ogan</em>和国土党领袖<em>Muharrem Ince</em> ，他们分别获得<strong>5.17%</strong>和<strong>0.43% 的</strong>支持率，尽管 Ince 此前已经退出竞选。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">谁是候选人？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">决一死战的两人是现任<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/erdogan-turkiye-does-not-intend-to-indulge-all-western-demands-1110473444.html" target="_blank">总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</a>和 CHP 领导人凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安：</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="list"><div class="article__list"><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div> 69 岁的埃尔多安曾在 2003 年至 2014 年担任土耳其总理，并在 1994 年至 1998 年担任伊斯坦布尔市长，他寻求在 5 月 14 日的选举中连续第三个总统任期。本周早些时候，奥根在决选中支持他。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>土耳其总统此前承诺，如果他在第二轮投票中获胜，“Turkiye [该国目前的人口] 的 8500 万人民中的每一个人都将获胜。”埃尔多安在向选民发表讲话时指出，公民“<strong>不应该给那些以国家统一和团结为目标的人机会</strong>”。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>他发誓，<strong>安卡拉将“打击所有邪恶网络</strong>，包括分离主义恐怖组织<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220630/turkey-received-guarantees-from-sweden-on-extradition-of-73-pkk-members-erdogan-says-1096838703.html" target="_blank">PKK [库尔德斯坦工人党]</a>及其分支机构，”他补充说，由于他的努力，库尔德工人党“无法再在土耳其行动”。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>埃尔多安承诺在土耳其控制的叙利亚北部实施住房项目后，将让大约一百万<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20210908/turkey-cares-about-afghan-refugees-but-isnt-ready-for-yet-another-influx-heres-why-1088871767.html" target="_blank">叙利亚难民</a>返回家园。他还强调，通过俄罗斯的调解努力改善叙利亚和土耳其之间的对话将有助于增加难民的“自愿”返回。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>在经济方面，土耳其总统表示，<strong>他希望在 2023 年将通胀水平降至 20%</strong> ，并在 2024 年将其降至 10% 以下，但明确表示政府将继续降低利率。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>在 2023 年 2 月发生的致命的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230208/devastating-earthquake-in-turkey-and-syria-in-moments-salvation-loss-and-miracle-1107068696.html" target="_blank">土耳其-叙利亚地震</a>中，他承诺向土耳其东南部的地震幸存者提供 20 年期限和两年宽限期的住房贷款。</div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>凯末尔·基利达罗格鲁：</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="list"><div class="article__list"><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div> 74 岁的 Kilicdaroglu 在 5 月 28 日决选之前的两周暂停期间将“打击恐怖主义”作为他的主要议题之一。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div> “恐怖主义将被打击，而不是谈判。任何针对土耳其国家和单一国家结构的政治和法律安排都是不允许的，”这位总统候选人说。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>他在第一轮会议前概述的其他主题包括<strong>非法移民问题</strong>，Kilicdaroglu 发誓要“为这个过程创造基础设施”，以便在两年内将他们遣返回国。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>这位 74 岁的老人还承诺制定常规经济政策，以稳定利率并对抗该国严重的恶性通货膨胀。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>他声称他可以从国外吸引多达<strong>3000 亿美元的投资</strong>，并辩称投资者只希望 Turkiye 的民主和信心来注入资金。</div><div class="article__list-item"><div class="article__list-label"></div>此外，Kilicdaroglu 承诺为在灾难中失去财产的地震幸存者提供免费住房。</div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">预测呢？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Center Arastirma 进行的一项最新民意调查显示， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/kilicdaroglu-getting-closer-to-erdogan-with-45-of-votes-in-presidential-election-1110360010.html" target="_blank">埃尔多安和基利达罗格鲁</a>有大致相等的机会宣扬决选胜利。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">调查显示， <strong>44.7%</strong>的受访者准备投票给热电联产领导人，而<strong>43.7%的人</strong>准备支持<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/turkish-fm-expects-erdogan-to-gain-over-56-in-election-runoff-1110553103.html" target="_blank">土耳其总统</a>。民意调查显示，其余 11.6% 的人要么尚未做出选择，要么根本不会去投票。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>与此同时，颇具影响力的土耳其民意调查机构 KONDA 透露，其最新调查显示，至少 47% 的受访者会在决选中对埃尔多安说“是”，而 Kilicdaroglu 将得到 42.2% 的支持。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据民意调查，大约 8.2% 的人尚未决定如何投票，2.6% 的人不打算投票。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 15:02:29 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/turkiye-presidential-election-runoff-who-when-where-what-to-expect-1110637609.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/turkiye-presidential-election-runoff-who-when-where-what-to-expect-1110637609.html<category>世界</category><category>总统决选</category><category>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</category><category>投票</category><category>2023 年土耳其总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Egyptian Archaeologists Unveil Two Largest Embalming Workshops Found to Date - Reports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110639160" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110638855_0:0:1280:913_1440x900_80_0_1_eba908846b762f6c1543896ac352c87f.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110638837" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/egyptian-archaeologists-unveil-two-largest-embalming-workshops-found-to-date---reports-1110639160.html?share-img=1110638837"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Zaman Ramazanov</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">左塞尔阶梯金字塔，萨卡拉</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Step Pyramid of Djoser, Saqqara - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="萨加拉左塞尔阶梯金字塔" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110638855_0:143:1280:863_1920x0_80_0_0_944ccadd572f9d9e51fa52b476d919c4.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110638855_0:143:1280:863_640x0_80_0_0_41cd0b6da0e5092fa540e6a60c84dad0.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110638855_0:143:1280:863_1280x0_80_0_0_316349278c10fc69f85618c92bcc7615.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1b/1110638855_0:143:1280:863_1920x0_80_0_0_944ccadd572f9d9e51fa52b476d919c4.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Zaman Ramazanov</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据开罗（人造卫星）网报道：据媒体援引埃及旅游和古物部长艾哈迈德·伊萨的话报道，埃及考古学家周六在位于开罗南部的萨卡拉古遗址揭开了两个人类和动物防腐作坊的面纱，这是迄今为止已知最大的作坊。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据地区广播公司报道，由埃及最高文物委员会主席穆斯塔法·瓦济里 (Mostafa Waziri) 率领的考察团还发现了两个墓地和一些其他文物。 Waziri 说，这些作坊的历史可以追溯到埃及第三十王朝和托勒密王朝初期，其中一个<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221126/gilt-laced-chat-with-the-gods-mummies-with-golden-tongues-dug-up-in-egypt-1104728537.html" target="_blank">用于制作人类木乃伊</a>，另一个用于对动物进行防腐处理。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">埃及考古团自 2018 年以来一直在萨卡拉进行挖掘。之前的挖掘发现了带有木乃伊动物的古墓，包括猫、幼狮、鳄鱼、猫鼬和圣甲虫。同年晚些时候，考古学家<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230307/riddle-me-this-egyptian-archeologists-unearth-smiling-sphinx-with-roman-emperors-face-1108140410.html" target="_blank">发掘了一座距今约 4,400 年的完好墓葬</a>，据信该墓葬属于一位生活在埃及第五王朝时期的高级官员。在那里还发现了其他可追溯到旧王国和新王国的墓葬。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20210118/egyptian-archaeologists-discover-50-ancient-coffins-decorated-with-excerpts-of-the-book-of-the-dead-1081798514.html" target="_blank">萨加拉 (Saqqara) 是最古老的墓地所在地</a>，其首批墓葬可追溯到埃及第一王朝，还有标志性的左塞尔阶梯金字塔 (Step Pyramid of Djoser)。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 14:37:44 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/egyptian-archaeologists-unveil-two-largest-embalming-workshops-found-to-date---reports-1110639160.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/egyptian-archaeologists-unveil-two-largest-embalming-workshops-found-to-date---reports-1110639160.html<category>超越政治</category><category>古埃及</category><category>古代历史</category><category>防腐</category><category>萨卡拉</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Henry Kissinger Turns 100: From Clandestine Ops Mastermind to Political Realist]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110637902" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18441/97/184419719_0:0:2873:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_d2194bb0f3d56e79a0775ec9a3bdb8d6.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="184419718" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html?share-img=184419718"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Alexey Nikolsky</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">亨利·基辛格</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Henry Kissinger - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="亨利·基辛格" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18441/97/184419719_0:0:2873:1617_1920x0_80_0_0_c6ac445a31f0407b183827889b274ef5.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18441/97/184419719_0:0:2873:1617_640x0_80_0_0_71970a6068488d7b71625a4e1cfa42fa.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18441/97/184419719_0:0:2873:1617_1280x0_80_0_0_977078864d6c382fac370cacc6f53c88.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/18441/97/184419719_0:0:2873:1617_1920x0_80_0_0_c6ac445a31f0407b183827889b274ef5.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Alexey Nikolsky</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶卡捷琳娜布林诺娃</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_ekaterina_blinova/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.blinova@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">这位以在 1980 年代推动美苏缓和和为结束冷战奠定基础而闻名的资深战略家于 5 月 27 日迎来了 100 岁生日。基辛格是谁，他的遗产是什么？ </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">亨利基辛格是美国政治学家和前美国国务卿。他以创立被称为“现实主义”的外交政策学说而闻名。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">无论地缘政治局势如何变化，基辛格继续坚持将俄罗斯视为全球平衡的“基本要素”，并呼吁与中国和平共处。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗得岛大学专门研究乌克兰和俄罗斯的政治学教授尼古拉·佩特罗 (Nicolai Petro) 表示，基辛格每次概述他的政治愿景时，都会将美国的利益放在心上。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “大多数人不明白，没有为了全人类的利益而追求的‘独立外交’，并且与追求权力脱节，”佩特罗告诉人造卫星。 “对于现实主义之父汉斯·摩根索来说，‘政治是对人的权力斗争，无论其最终目标是什么，权力都是其直接目标’。基辛格比大多数人更了解这一点。他的最新著作《领导力：六项研究》 《世界战略》是对六位政治家的赞歌，他们毕生致力于为本国政府谋取利益。对于像基辛格这样的经典现实主义者来说，这是外交成功的​​顶峰。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110637902" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html?share-block=1110637905" data-title="&amp;quot;Most people don’t understand that there is no &amp;#x27;independent diplomacy&amp;#x27; pursued for the benefit of all humanity and disconnected from the pursuits of power,&amp;quot; Petro told Sputnik. &amp;quot;For the Father of Realism, Hans Morgenthau, &amp;#x27;Politics is a struggle for power over men and whatever its ultimate aim may be, power is its immediate goal&amp;#x27;. Kissinger understood this better than most. His latest book &amp;#x27;Leadership: Six Studies in World Strategy&amp;#x27;, is a paean to six statesmen who devoted their lives to the achievement of advantages for their national governments. For a classical Realist like Kissinger, this is the pinnacle of diplomatic success.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">基辛格是谁？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">亨利·基辛格 1923 年出生于德国的一个犹太家庭。纳粹在该国夺取政权后，基辛格移民到美国，逃离希特勒政权的反犹太政策，并在纽约定居。第二次世界大战期间，亨利·基辛格 (Henry Kissinger) 在美国陆军服役，担任德语翻译。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">战后，这位准战略家在被占领的西德的陆军反情报部队任职。根据普利策奖获奖记者西摩赫什的说法，基辛格被分配到一个部门，其职能特别包括招募前纳粹情报官员。美国将它们用于苏联集团内部的反苏行动。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> 1950 年代，基辛格担任包括国防部运筹学办公室在内的多个政府机构的顾问，而在 1952 年，他被任命为心理战略委员会主任的助手，专门从事秘密心理和准军事行动。当时，据称基辛格还与美伊政策的设计师、总统德怀特·艾森豪威尔负责冷战规划的特别助理纳尔逊·洛克菲勒关系密切。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 1968 年，时任总统当选人理查德尼克松任命基辛格为其国家安全顾问一职。因此，从 1969 年到 1976 年，基辛格在塑造尼克松总统和杰拉尔德福特总统领导下的美国外交政策方面发挥了明显的作用。随后几年，他继续以美国政府外交政策顾问的身份工作。他仍然是一位政治重量级人物，美国领导人对他的建议表示同情。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">基辛格的批评者称他为<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20211202/gt-investigates-us-war-mongering-under-guise-of-democracy-inflicts-untold-damage-on-the-world-1091196319.html" target="_blank">“战争贩子”</a> ，因为他在 1973 年推翻了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20200911/waiting-for-spring-the-1973-chilean-coup-and-a-lesson-for-the-left-1080430687.html" target="_blank">智利总统萨尔瓦多·阿连德，</a>为阿根廷军政府残酷清洗左翼分子开了“绿灯”， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220810/august-10th-remembering-a-day-of-tragedy-for-the-people-of-vietnam-1099439710.html" target="_blank">越南战争</a>期间有争议的政策（从升级冲突到尝试结束它），美国在越南战争期间轰炸柬埔寨平民，并让中国与苏联对抗。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">同时，正是基辛格推动了与中华人民共和国的复交，开创了对苏缓和政策，最终导致了冷战的结束。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">美苏缓和与苏联解体</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美苏缓和的主要问题是两个核大国之间的军备限制条约。旨在限制搭载核武器的远程或洲际弹道导弹军备竞赛的战略武器限制谈判（SALT）始于1969年。SALT I和SALT II分别于1972年和1979年由美国和苏联签署，基辛格在推动美国方面的战略方面发挥了重要作用。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 80 年代，美国总统罗纳德·里根任命基辛格在其外国情报顾问委员会和综合长期战略委员会任职。 1987 年，里根和苏联领导人米哈伊尔·戈尔巴乔夫签署了《中程核力量条约》(INF)，为数十年的敌意铺平了道路。 1989年11月柏林墙的倒塌成为冷战结束的明显标志。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110637902" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102795/64/1027956492_0:0:2040:1820_1440x900_80_0_1_952d22d0aaffed53a271ba2c5692658a.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1027956491" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html?share-img=1027956491"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Archiv</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">1989 年 11 月 10 日，柏林墙开放前一天，人们在勃兰登堡门前的柏林墙上行走</span></div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="People walking on the Berlin wall in front of the Brandenburg gate after opening one day before, Nov. 10, 1989 - Sputnik International, 1920, 27.05.2023" title="1989 年 11 月 10 日，一天前开放后，人们走在勃兰登堡门前的柏林墙上" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102795/64/1027956492_0:0:2040:1820_1920x0_80_0_0_70ac0ae74ab24cb0de4e5a1f1ab78471.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221713%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1713" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102795/64/1027956492_0:0:2040:1820_640x0_80_0_0_813b26dcd0705899a185304418ec82f9.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102795/64/1027956492_0:0:2040:1820_1280x0_80_0_0_0530847a4e9412cd11526ddb66a0860b.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102795/64/1027956492_0:0:2040:1820_1920x0_80_0_0_70ac0ae74ab24cb0de4e5a1f1ab78471.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet=""> 1989 年 11 月 10 日，一天前开放后，人们走在勃兰登堡门前的柏林墙上</div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Archiv </div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 1989 年 1 月，即 SALT II 签署十年后，作为美国三边委员会倡议的一部分，亨利·基辛格 (Henry Kissinger) 和他的同事前往苏联会见戈尔巴乔夫 (Gorbachev)。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该小组和戈尔巴乔夫讨论了两个大国之间的共存问题，以及苏联融入世界经济的路线图、寻找两国之间的合作形式以及为未来合作建立法律和经济基础。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，1991年苏联不复存在，戈尔巴乔夫-基辛格的计划破灭，伴随着北约东扩、华盛顿的海外战争和政权更迭行动，开启了美国单极时代的大门。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “冷战后的破坏循环始于错误的希望，即强加美国霸权可以创造全球和平。这导致忽视传统平衡，追求被误解为全人类利益的国家利益，”佩特罗说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “因此，追求平衡和拒绝霸权是外交政策成功的关键，现实主义者说，因为单靠权力的运用只会导致升级。现实主义假设世界充满了永远无法解决的矛盾，政治家们应该认识到，无法逃避试图通过胁迫行善而不可避免地导致的邪恶（……）因此，回归基辛格现实主义将是朝着正确方向迈出的一步，恢复对彼此利益的相互尊重，”他指出。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110637902" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html?share-block=1110637925" data-title="&quot;The pursuit of balance, and the rejection of hegemony are thus the key to the success of foreign policy, say Realists, because the application of power alone will only lead to escalation. Realism assumes the world is full of contradictions that will never be resolved, and statesmen should recognize that there is no escape from the evil that inevitably results from trying to do good through coercion (…) A return to Kissingerian Realism would therefore be a step in the right direction, restoring mutual respect for each other’s interests,&quot; he pointed out."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">基辛格对中俄关系的看法</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在过去的三十年里，美俄关系被证明是崎岖不平且充满争议的，最终导致由美国及其北约盟国领导的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220612/henry-kissinger-says-us-infinitely-more-polarized-today-than-during-vietnam-war-1096237196.html" target="_blank">乌克兰正在进行的代理人战争</a>。现任拜登政府及其前任政府似乎让基辛格几十年的缓和努力付之东流。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “如果美国通过北约的扩张在欧洲寻求平衡而不是霸权，俄罗斯很可能会接受现状。现在，经典现实主义者说，美国又在与中国犯同样的错误，”教授解释。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110637902" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html?share-block=1110637929" data-title="&amp;quot;Had the United States sought balance rather than hegemony in Europe through the expansion of NATO, Russia would have most likely accepted the status quo. Now, say classical realists, the United States is making exactly the same mistake again with China,&amp;quot; the professor explained."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">基辛格认为，俄乌冲突主要是由华盛顿推动乌克兰加入北约的计划引发的。 “我认为决定……开放乌克兰在北约的成员资格是非常错误的，”这位资深外交官本月早些时候告诉《经济学人》。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而与此同时，他现在正在鼓吹<strong>乌克兰加入北约</strong>。他认为，乌克兰既需要保护，也需要克制。 <em>“如果我与普京交谈，我会告诉他，他在北约与乌克兰的关系也更安全，”</em>他在最近的采访中说。 <em>“我们现在已经将乌克兰武装到一个地步，它将成为欧洲武装最精良的国家，也是欧洲战略经验最少的国家。”</em></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位老外交官还称赞中国和平解决乌克兰问题，并警告拜登政府不要挑起与中华人民共和国的冲突。据他说，华盛顿和北京之间的和平共处与合作是可能的。另一方面，中苏分裂的始作俑者坚持 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20170122/kissinger-trump-russia-1049877160.html" target="_blank">俄罗斯和中国不能很好地合作</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">从佩特罗的观点来看，不存在与追求权力脱节的外交，人们可能会认为基辛格的愿景反映了对美国最好的是什么。与此同时，俄罗斯和中国一直在<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/pepe-escobar-eurasian-heartland-rises-to-challenge-the-west-1110600622.html" target="_blank">实施他们自己的愿景</a>，在他们最近的国家和全球安全理论中有所概述。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 27 May 2023 14:27:27 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230527/henry-kissinger-turns-100-from-clandestine-ops-mastermind-to-political-realist-1110637902.html<category>分析</category><category>亨利·基辛格</category><category>米哈伊尔·戈尔巴乔夫</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>中国</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>北约</category><category>越南战争</category><category>柏林墙</category><category>苏联</category><category>冷战</category><category>柬埔寨</category><category>我们</category><category>亚太地区</category><category>欧洲</category><category>观点</category></item></channel></rss>